PHISHING EMAIL SAMPLE ANALYSIS – SAMPLE 4

Subject:
Instagram Alert – Unusual Login Attempt

Sender Email:
insta@gmail.com

Greeting:
Dear User,


EMAIL MESSAGE

We noticed a suspicious login attempt on your
Instagram account from an unknown device.

For security reasons, your account access may be
limited until you confirm your identity.

Please verify your account immediately using the
link below:

http://instagram-security-check.com

If you do not confirm your account within 12 hours,
your account may be temporarily suspended.

Thank you,
Instagram Security Team


PHISHING INDICATORS IDENTIFIED

1. Unofficial Sender Email
The sender address "insta@gmail.com" is not an
official Instagram domain. Legitimate emails from
Instagram usually come from addresses ending with
@instagram.com.

2. Generic Greeting
The email uses "Dear User" instead of addressing
the recipient by their real username.

3. Urgent Security Message
The email pressures the user to verify their
account quickly by threatening account suspension.

4. Suspicious Link
The link "http://instagram-security-check.com"
is not an official Instagram domain and could
redirect users to a fake login page.


EMAIL CLASSIFICATION
Type: Phishing Email
Risk Level: HIGH


ANALYSIS SUMMARY

This email impersonates Instagram and attempts to
trick users into verifying their account through a
malicious link. If users enter their credentials on
the fake website, attackers can steal login details
and gain unauthorized access to the account.

Users should always verify account alerts by logging
into Instagram directly through the official app or
website.
